"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-10-China-bringing-home-more-gold-on-Day-14-of-Paris-Olympics-1vWwT2q50Jy-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  Gold medallists China's Wang Chuqin, China's Ma Long and China's Fan Zhendong pose with their medals on the podium of the men's table tennis team event at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: WANG Zhao / AFP  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Ma Long became the country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most decorated Olympian on Friday, Aug. 9, winning his sixth gold medal of his athletic career alongside teammates Wang Chuqin and Fan Zhendong, as they beat Sweden in table tennis.  Ma said he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s glad to get the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cperfect ending\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d in his last Olympics.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis is my last Olympics and the experience is perfect. I feel very proud and lucky,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Ma.  China's gold medallists Xu Shixiao and China's Sun Mengya celebrate winning in the women's canoe double 500m final of the canoe sprint competition at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: Bertrand GUAY / AFP  Xu Shixiao and Sun Mengya also won another gold for China in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s canoe double 500-meter final at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium. Ukraine took silver, and Canada picked up the bronze.  China's Chen Yiwen competes in the women's 3m springboard diving final during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: Oli SCARFF / AFP  Chen Yiwen also won the gold medal in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 3-meter springboard, extending China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s winning streak in the 2024 Games diving events to seven. She was the only diver on Friday that scored over 70 points in each round. Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Maddison Keeney took silver and China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Chang Yani won the bronze medal.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMy heart was beating so fast from the warm-up all the way through the last dive,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Chen told reporters after the event. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThen when I finished the last dive I suddenly calmed down, like I had just let out a long breath.  Back on land, China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Wu Yu claimed gold in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 50 kg boxing championship while teammate Yang Liu took home the silver medal in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 66 kg boxing final after losing to Algeria\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Imane Khelif.  Algeria's Imane Khelif and China's Yang Liu (Blue) compete in the women's 66kg final boxing match during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: MOHD RASFAN / AFP  Canada won the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic 4x100 meter relay for the second time on Friday after the United States fumbled a changeover and was disqualified.  The United States did secure a gold medal in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4x100 meters relay, capturing their 12th title in the event.  U.S.' Sha'Carri Richardson crosses the finish line to win the women's 4x100m relay final of the athletics event at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: Antonin THUILLIER / AFP  Melissa Jefferson, Twanisha Terry, Paris Olympic 200m champion Gabby Thomas and Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri Richardson clocked 41.78 seconds for the U.S.  Making Olympic history, China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Liu Qingyi (aka 671) pop and locked her way to the bronze medal in the B-Girls breaking on Friday, Aug 9, as breakdancing made its debut at this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Games. Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Ami Yuasa took home gold while Lithuania\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dominika Banevic took silver.  China's Liu Qingyi, known as 671 competes in the Women's Breaking dance Round robin of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: Odd ANDERSEN / AFP  Yuasa, known as B-Girl Ami, laid down a series of halos to seal the 3-0 win which brought the crowd at La Concorde to their feet.  Japan's Ami Yuasa known as Ami competes in the Women's Breaking dance gold medal battle of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: Odd ANDERSEN / AFP  China also took home silver in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s field hockey, losing to the Netherlands after a penalty shootout following a 1-1 draw in regulation. The win gave the Dutch a hockey double after Thursday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s win. The Chinese team opened the scoring in the sixth minute when forward Chen Yi turned midfielder Dan Wen\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s pass past Veenendaal, stunning the ranks of Dutch fans packed into the stands.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Song Jiayuan won the bronze in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s shot put final, while Germany\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Yemisi Ogunleye won the gold and New Zealand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Maddison-Lee Wesche claimed the silver.  Brazil's #02 Eduarda Santos Lisboa and Brazil's #01 Ana Patricia Silva Ramos celebrate after winning the women's gold medal beach volleyball match between Brazil and Canada during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on August 9, 2024. Photo: Jeff PACHOUD / AFP  In the last game of the day, Brazilian pair Ana Patricia Silva and Eduarda Santos won gold in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s beach volleyball, taking the victory after beating Canada in three tense sets.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"